<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,1500,1886]" box="[264,781,1500,1526]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,416,1500,1526]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Description.</emphasis>
Body length. Female. 6.7 mm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,1500,1886]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Coryphe elongate, lateral margins keel-shaped and concave medially, anterior margin narrowly rounded, posterior margin obtusely angulate (fig. 
<number box="[981,996,1580,1606]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="3.0">3</number>
b). Fore wing reaches hind margin of pygofer; median simple. Metatarsomere I with 
<number box="[938,953,1620,1646]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="6.0">6</number>
intermediate socle setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,1500,1886]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,454,1660,1686]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Coloration.</emphasis>
General coloration yellowish light brown (fig. 
<number box="[1059,1074,1660,1686]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="3.0">3</number>
a). Fore wings with brown markings. Teeth and socle setae of hind legs with black apices.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,1500,1886]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Female genitalia. Anal tube gradually narrows to apex (in dorsal view). Gonoplacs triangular, elongate, with tapered apices (fig. 
<number box="[795,812,1780,1806]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="7.0">7</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
